    <p>
        During Eta Kappa Nu 2010 National Conference, students are divided into teams.
        Each team consists of students from different universities.
        Within 3 days, each team is expected to design, program and compete in Sumobot competition.
        Each team has different parts of Lego Mindstorm and programming is done in LabVIEW.
    </p>
    <p>
        Link to WSU page:
        <a href="https://www.wichita.edu/academics/engineering/hkn_epsilonxi/hkn_events/student_conferance.php">2010 HKN Student Conference</a>
    </p>
    <p>
        On the first day, I was just having fun making the Lego below which is not designed for competition.
    </p>
