    <p>
        The second day, my Lego was rebuilt for competition.
        We did quick research and decided on a robot equipped with ramp in the front.
        One of our team members named it "Wally" (inspired by Wall-e).
        I was in charge of programming it since I'm the only one majoring in Computer Science in my team.
        It took me most of the second night to figure out how to code in LabVIEW and upload the program to the robot.
        At the end, competition didn't start well for us but my team managed to get runner up.
